commitResults.messageBody:
The loading of the data happens automatically when the program
first starts by calling `FileReaderWriter.loadMediTrackerData`.

Some error handling is provided to ensure that the program does not
crash when starting up for the first time, or when reading corrupt JSON
save file, and instead treat them as invalid and the program will run
with a clean slate.

commitResults.messageBody: feat: Add save and load data for daily medication manager
fix(bug): Update daily medication name on modify

- Used ArgumentName as the source of string rather than typing another
copy when taking info from the Medication object,
so future references will be consistent in naming

- SLAP-ed the appropriate functionalities into its individual methods.

The JSON Importer class now does not create the Medication objects
directly. Instead, it now passes a List<Map<String,String>> for the
MedicationManager to handle. The manager shall be responsible in
parsing and converting the data to the appropriate format.

Previously it was the job of the JsonImporter to create Medication
and populate MedicationManager.
The role has now shifted to MedicationManger.

commitResults.messageBody:
As far as possible, the use of `File` and `String` for file path shall
be minimised and replaced with `Path` instead. At the same time, reduce
the need to throw exceptions if they can be handled locally and give
a more meaningful return value.

This is to help support the upcoming feature on saving to and loading
from different locations of the local filesystem.

The load command also relies on the same sequence of checks as the
save command, hence the abstraction now.

Adds support for the `load` command, less the part on the actual
replacement of the existing data.
